<h2>Results</h2>

<p>
	This table explains the performance of each variant in the AB test. If the conversion rate
	of the variant is higher than the control we can use the significant calculations below to 
	tell us whether we can be confidence in it's out-performance.
</p>

<div id="ab__container"></div>

<p>
	This table helps to intpret the significance A/B test results.
</p>
<p>
	In general, the smaller the variation between the control and variant the
	larger the sample or test duration needs to be in order to increase our
	confidence in the result. 
</p>

